<!-- ========== ORIGINS ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Origins: From Soviet Research Labs to Modern Nootropics</h2>

<p>The development of both Selank and Semax traces back to Soviet-era research programs aimed at enhancing cognitive performance and stress resilience. The work was led by Nikolai Myasoedov and his colleagues at the Russian Academy of Sciences, starting in the 1980s and continuing through the post-Soviet period.</p>

<p>The approach was clever. Rather than designing entirely novel molecules, the researchers took naturally occurring peptides and modified them to improve stability and bioactivity.</p>

<div class="g2">
